{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3941,"text":"Blah blah blah blah blah."},{"time":6472,"text":"Blah blah blah blah,"},{"time":8399,"text":"blah blah, blah blah blah blah blah blah."},{"time":10994,"text":"Blah blah blah, blah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14997,"text":"So what the hell was that?"},{"time":17170,"text":"Well, you don't know\nbecause you couldn't understand it."},{"time":21320,"text":"It wasn't clear."},{"time":24530,"text":"But hopefully, it was said\nwith enough conviction"},{"time":27768,"text":"that it was at least\nalluringly mysterious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32792,"text":"Clarity or mystery?"},{"time":35973,"text":"I'm balancing these two things\nin my daily work as a graphic designer,"},{"time":40199,"text":"as well as my daily life as a New Yorker"},{"time":45031,"text":"every day,"},{"time":46561,"text":"and there are two elements\nthat absolutely fascinate me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51028,"text":"Here's an example."},{"time":53390,"text":"Now, how many people know what this is?"},{"time":59703,"text":"Okay. Now how many people\nknow what this is?"},{"time":64727,"text":"Okay. Thanks to two more deft strokes\nby the genius Charles M. Schulz,"},{"time":72410,"text":"we now have seven deft strokes\nthat in and of themselves"},{"time":75454,"text":"create an entire emotional life,"},{"time":78984,"text":"one that has enthralled\nhundreds of millions of fans"},{"time":81863,"text":"for over 50 years."},{"time":83906,"text":"This is actually a cover of a book"},{"time":86420,"text":"that I designed about the work\nof Schulz and his art,"},{"time":89711,"text":"which will be coming out this fall,"},{"time":92497,"text":"and that is the entire cover."},{"time":94378,"text":"There is no other typographic information\nor visual information on the front,"},{"time":99324,"text":"and the name of the book\nis \"Only What's Necessary.\""},{"time":103317,"text":"So this is sort of symbolic about\nthe decisions I have to make every day"},{"time":108790,"text":"about the design that I'm perceiving,"},{"time":112706,"text":"and the design I'm creating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115525,"text":"So clarity."},{"time":117332,"text":"Clarity gets to the point."},{"time":119421,"text":"It's blunt. It's honest. It's sincere."},{"time":123748,"text":"We ask ourselves this.\n[\"When should you be clear?\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":127370,"text":"Now, something like this,\nwhether we can read it or not,"},{"time":132818,"text":"needs to be really, really clear."},{"time":136418,"text":"Is it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140586,"text":"This is a rather recent example\nof urban clarity that I just love,"},{"time":147284,"text":"mainly because I'm always late\nand I am always in a hurry."},{"time":152742,"text":"So when these meters started showing up\na couple of years ago on street corners,"},{"time":159288,"text":"I was thrilled, because now I finally knew"},{"time":162748,"text":"how many seconds I had\nto get across the street"},{"time":165673,"text":"before I got run over by a car."},{"time":168553,"text":"Six? I can do that. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173475,"text":"So let's look at the yin\nto the clarity yang,"},{"time":177283,"text":"and that is mystery."},{"time":180812,"text":"Mystery is a lot more complicated\nby its very definition."},{"time":186176,"text":"Mystery demands to be decoded,"},{"time":189659,"text":"and when it's done right,\nwe really, really want to."},{"time":192643,"text":"[\"When should you be mysterious?\"]"},{"time":194303,"text":"In World War II, the Germans\nreally, really wanted to decode this,"},{"time":200107,"text":"and they couldn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202731,"text":"Here's an example of a design\nthat I've done recently"},{"time":205912,"text":"for a novel by Haruki Murakami,"},{"time":208234,"text":"who I've done design work for\nfor over 20 years now,"},{"time":211438,"text":"and this is a novel about a young man\nwho has four dear friends"},{"time":217150,"text":"who all of a sudden,\nafter their freshman year of college,"},{"time":220819,"text":"completely cut him off\nwith no explanation,"},{"time":224116,"text":"and he is devastated."},{"time":225973,"text":"And the friends' names each have\na connotation in Japanese to a color."},{"time":231376,"text":"So there's Mr. Red, there's Mr. Blue,\nthere's Ms. White, and Ms. Black."},{"time":236770,"text":"Tsukuru Tazaki, his name\ndoes not correspond to a color,"},{"time":240160,"text":"so his nickname is Colorless, and\nas he's looking back on their friendship,"},{"time":244610,"text":"he recalls that they were like\nfive fingers on a hand."},{"time":247776,"text":"So I created this sort of abstract\nrepresentation of this,"},{"time":252257,"text":"but there's a lot more going on\nunderneath the surface of the story,"},{"time":256437,"text":"and there's more going on underneath\nthe surface of the jacket."},{"time":261110,"text":"The four fingers are now four train lines"},{"time":265515,"text":"in the Tokyo subway system,"},{"time":267582,"text":"which has significance within the story."},{"time":270813,"text":"And then you have\nthe colorless subway line"},{"time":273610,"text":"intersecting with each\nof the other colors,"},{"time":276173,"text":"which basically he does\nlater on in the story."},{"time":278820,"text":"He catches up with each of these people"},{"time":280802,"text":"to find out why they treated him\nthe way they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284332,"text":"And so this is the three-dimensional\nfinished product"},{"time":288558,"text":"sitting on my desk in my office,"},{"time":290879,"text":"and what I was hoping for here\nis that you'll simply be allured"},{"time":295546,"text":"by the mystery of what this looks like,"},{"time":299401,"text":"and will want to read it"},{"time":302196,"text":"to decode and find out and make more clear\nwhy it looks the way it does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308163,"text":"[\"The Visual Vernacular.\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309858,"text":"This is a way to use a more\nfamiliar kind of mystery."},{"time":314177,"text":"What does this mean?"},{"time":315938,"text":"This is what it means.\n[\"Make it look like something else.\"]"},{"time":318772,"text":"The visual vernacular is the way\nwe are used to seeing a certain thing"},{"time":323302,"text":"applied to something else so that\nwe see it in a different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327691,"text":"This is an approach I wanted to take\nto a book of essays by David Sedaris"},{"time":331840,"text":"that had this title at the time.\n[\"All the Beauty You Will Ever Need\"]"},{"time":335211,"text":"Now, the challenge here was that\nthis title actually means nothing."},{"time":339402,"text":"It's not connected to any\nof the essays in the book."},{"time":342792,"text":"It came to the author's boyfriend\nin a dream."},{"time":347993,"text":"Thank you very much, so -- (Laughter) --\nso usually, I am creating a design"},{"time":353659,"text":"that is in some way based on the text,\nbut this is all the text there is."},{"time":357722,"text":"So you've got this mysterious title\nthat really doesn't mean anything,"},{"time":362111,"text":"so I was trying to think:"},{"time":364610,"text":"Where might I see a bit of mysterious text\nthat seems to mean something but doesn't?"},{"time":370848,"text":"And sure enough, not long after,"},{"time":373255,"text":"one evening after a Chinese meal,"},{"time":376570,"text":"this arrived, and I thought,\n\"Ah, bing, ideagasm!\" (Laughter)"},{"time":383472,"text":"I've always loved the hilariously\nmysterious tropes of fortune cookies"},{"time":388673,"text":"that seem to mean something extremely deep"},{"time":391575,"text":"but when you think about them -- if you\nthink about them -- they really don't."},{"time":395662,"text":"This says, \"Hardly anyone knows how much\nis gained by ignoring the future.\""},{"time":402537,"text":"Thank you. (Laughter)"},{"time":405389,"text":"But we can take this visual vernacular\nand apply it to Mr. Sedaris,"},{"time":411046,"text":"and we are so familiar\nwith how fortune cookie fortunes look"},{"time":416657,"text":"that we don't even need\nthe bits of the cookie anymore."},{"time":419424,"text":"We're just seeing this strange thing"},{"time":422419,"text":"and we know we love David Sedaris,"},{"time":424416,"text":"and so we're hoping that\nwe're in for a good time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427760,"text":"[\"'Fraud' Essays by David Rakoff\"]\nDavid Rakoff was a wonderful writer"},{"time":431048,"text":"and he called his first book \"Fraud\""},{"time":434211,"text":"because he was getting sent\non assignments by magazines"},{"time":438171,"text":"to do things that he\nwas not equipped to do."},{"time":440841,"text":"So he was this skinny little urban guy"},{"time":443163,"text":"and GQ magazine would send him\ndown the Colorado River"},{"time":446762,"text":"whitewater rafting to see\nif he would survive."},{"time":451378,"text":"And then he would write about it,\nand he felt that he was a fraud"},{"time":454679,"text":"and that he was misrepresenting himself."},{"time":456978,"text":"And so I wanted the cover of this book\nto also misrepresent itself"},{"time":461645,"text":"and then somehow show\na reader reacting to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466916,"text":"This led me to graffiti."},{"time":470167,"text":"I'm fascinated by graffiti."},{"time":472210,"text":"I think anybody who lives\nin an urban environment"},{"time":474903,"text":"encounters graffiti all the time,\nand there's all different sorts of it."},{"time":478943,"text":"This is a picture I took\non the Lower East Side"},{"time":482550,"text":"of just a transformer box on the sidewalk"},{"time":485398,"text":"and it's been tagged like crazy."},{"time":487372,"text":"Now whether you look at this and think,\n\"Oh, that's a charming urban affectation,\""},{"time":492991,"text":"or you look at it and say,\n\"That's illegal abuse of property,\""},{"time":497379,"text":"the one thing I think we can all agree on"},{"time":499724,"text":"is that you cannot read it."},{"time":502905,"text":"Right? There is no clear message here."},{"time":506458,"text":"There is another kind of graffiti\nthat I find far more interesting,"},{"time":511682,"text":"which I call editorial graffiti."},{"time":514538,"text":"This is a picture I took recently\nin the subway,"},{"time":518744,"text":"and sometimes you see\nlots of prurient, stupid stuff,"},{"time":522610,"text":"but I thought this was interesting,\nand this is a poster that is saying"},{"time":527517,"text":"rah-rah Airbnb,"},{"time":529747,"text":"and someone has taken a Magic Marker"},{"time":532510,"text":"and has editorialized about\nwhat they think about it."},{"time":536434,"text":"And it got my attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539266,"text":"So I was thinking, how do we\napply this to this book?"},{"time":542692,"text":"So I get the book by this person,\nand I start reading it, and I'm thinking,"},{"time":548405,"text":"this guy is not who he says \nhe is; he's a fraud."},{"time":553079,"text":"And I get out a red Magic Marker,"},{"time":556540,"text":"and out of frustration just\nscribble this across the front."},{"time":561151,"text":"Design done. (Laughter)"},{"time":565815,"text":"And they went for it! (Laughter)"},{"time":570190,"text":"Author liked it, publisher liked it,"},{"time":572107,"text":"and that is how the book\nwent out into the world,"},{"time":574824,"text":"and it was really fun to see\npeople reading this on the subway"},{"time":579723,"text":"and walking around with it\nand what have you,"},{"time":581859,"text":"and they all sort of looked\nlike they were crazy."},{"time":585760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588590,"text":"[\"'Perfidia' a novel by James Ellroy\"]\nOkay, James Ellroy, amazing crime writer,"},{"time":592633,"text":"a good friend, I've worked\nwith him for many years."},{"time":595117,"text":"He is probably best known as the author"},{"time":597325,"text":"of \"The Black Dahlia\"\nand \"L.A. Confidential.\""},{"time":600295,"text":"His most recent novel was called this,\nwhich is a very mysterious name"},{"time":605150,"text":"that I'm sure a lot of people know\nwhat it means, but a lot of people don't."},{"time":608756,"text":"And it's a story about a Japanese-American\ndetective in Los Angeles in 1941"},{"time":615814,"text":"investigating a murder."},{"time":617834,"text":"And then Pearl Harbor happens,"},{"time":620247,"text":"and as if his life\nwasn't difficult enough,"},{"time":623357,"text":"now the race relations\nhave really ratcheted up,"},{"time":628200,"text":"and then the Japanese-American\ninternment camps are quickly created,"},{"time":632718,"text":"and there's lots of tension"},{"time":634738,"text":"and horrible stuff as he's still\ntrying to solve this murder."},{"time":638824,"text":"And so I did at first think\nvery literally about this in terms of"},{"time":644656,"text":"all right, we'll take Pearl Harbor\nand we'll add it to Los Angeles"},{"time":648539,"text":"and we'll make this apocalyptic dawn\non the horizon of the city."},{"time":656146,"text":"And so that's a picture from Pearl Harbor"},{"time":658561,"text":"just grafted onto Los Angeles."},{"time":661625,"text":"My editor in chief said,\n\"You know, it's interesting"},{"time":664899,"text":"but I think you can do better\nand I think you can make it simpler.\""},{"time":670286,"text":"And so I went back\nto the drawing board, as I often do."},{"time":674506,"text":"But also, being alive to my surroundings,"},{"time":679197,"text":"I work in a high-rise in Midtown,"},{"time":682830,"text":"and every night,\nbefore I leave the office,"},{"time":686500,"text":"I have to push this button to get out,"},{"time":688745,"text":"and the big heavy glass doors open\nand I can get onto the elevator."},{"time":692483,"text":"And one night, all of a sudden,"},{"time":695979,"text":"I looked at this and I saw it in a way\nthat I hadn't really noticed it before."},{"time":701750,"text":"Big red circle, danger."},{"time":704279,"text":"And I thought this was so obvious"},{"time":707158,"text":"that it had to have been\ndone a zillion times,"},{"time":709875,"text":"and so I did a Google image search,\nand I couldn't find another book cover"},{"time":714449,"text":"that looked quite like this,"},{"time":716608,"text":"and so this is really\nwhat solved the problem,"},{"time":719232,"text":"and graphically it's more interesting"},{"time":721763,"text":"and creates a bigger tension\nbetween the idea"},{"time":725989,"text":"of a certain kind of sunrise\ncoming up over L.A. and America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731506,"text":"[\"'Gulp' A tour of the human\ndigestive system by Mary Roach.\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":734492,"text":"Mary Roach is an amazing writer"},{"time":736530,"text":"who takes potentially mundane\nscientific subjects"},{"time":740152,"text":"and makes them not mundane at all;\nshe makes them really fun."},{"time":743540,"text":"So in this particular case,"},{"time":745167,"text":"it's about the human digestive system."},{"time":748279,"text":"So I'm trying to figure out what\nis the cover of this book going to be."},{"time":754141,"text":"This is a self-portrait. (Laughter)"},{"time":757845,"text":"Every morning I look at myself\nin the medicine cabinet mirror"},{"time":763905,"text":"to see if my tongue is black."},{"time":766622,"text":"And if it's not, I'm good to go."},{"time":770170,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":775185,"text":"I recommend you all do this."},{"time":778296,"text":"But I also started thinking,\nhere's our introduction."},{"time":782243,"text":"Right? Into the human digestive system."},{"time":785962,"text":"But I think what we can all agree on"},{"time":788210,"text":"is that actual photographs\nof human mouths, at least based on this,"},{"time":792460,"text":"are off-putting. (Laughter)"},{"time":796244,"text":"So for the cover, then,\nI had this illustration done"},{"time":800145,"text":"which is literally more palatable"},{"time":802374,"text":"and reminds us that it's best\nto approach the digestive system"},{"time":806902,"text":"from this end."},{"time":809200,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":811847,"text":"I don't even have to complete\nthe sentence. All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815533,"text":"[\"Unuseful mystery\"]"},{"time":817079,"text":"What happens when clarity\nand mystery get mixed up?"},{"time":821516,"text":"And we see this all the time."},{"time":823489,"text":"This is what I call unuseful mystery."},{"time":825997,"text":"I go down into the subway --\nI take the subway a lot --"},{"time":828946,"text":"and this piece of paper\nis taped to a girder."},{"time":834590,"text":"Right? And now I'm thinking, uh-oh,"},{"time":838243,"text":"and the train's about to come and I'm\ntrying to figure out what this means,"},{"time":842120,"text":"and thanks a lot."},{"time":844914,"text":"Part of the problem here is that\nthey've compartmentalized the information"},{"time":848914,"text":"in a way they think is helpful,\nand frankly, I don't think it is at all."},{"time":852420,"text":"So this is mystery we do not need."},{"time":855694,"text":"What we need is useful clarity,\nso just for fun, I redesigned this."},{"time":863780,"text":"This is using all the same elements."},{"time":866259,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":869532,"text":"Thank you. I am still waiting\nfor a call from the MTA. (Laughter)"},{"time":874447,"text":"You know, I'm actually not even\nusing more colors than they use."},{"time":877506,"text":"They just didn't even bother\nto make the 4 and the 5 green,"},{"time":880803,"text":"those idiots. (Laughter)"},{"time":884851,"text":"So the first thing we see\nis that there is a service change,"},{"time":887920,"text":"and then, in two complete sentences\nwith a beginning, a middle and an end,"},{"time":891613,"text":"it tells us what the change is\nand what's going to be happening."},{"time":896383,"text":"Call me crazy! (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":901630,"text":"[\"Useful mystery\"]\nAll right."},{"time":904161,"text":"Now, here is a piece\nof mystery that I love:"},{"time":909841,"text":"packaging."},{"time":911498,"text":"This redesign of the Diet Coke can"},{"time":914772,"text":"by Turner Duckworth\nis to me truly a piece of art."},{"time":920200,"text":"It's a work of art. It's beautiful."},{"time":923716,"text":"But part of what makes it\nso heartening to me as a designer"},{"time":926893,"text":"is that he's taken the visual\nvernacular of Diet Coke --"},{"time":931351,"text":"the typefaces, the colors,\nthe silver background --"},{"time":934889,"text":"and he's reduced them\nto their most essential parts,"},{"time":939974,"text":"so it's like going back\nto the Charlie Brown face."},{"time":942714,"text":"It's like, how can you give them just\nenough information so they know what it is"},{"time":946661,"text":"but giving them the credit\nfor the knowledge that they already have"},{"time":950539,"text":"about this thing?"},{"time":952396,"text":"It looks great, and you would go\ninto a delicatessen"},{"time":956181,"text":"and all of a sudden see that on the shelf,\nand it's wonderful."},{"time":960631,"text":"Which makes the next thing --"},{"time":964330,"text":"[\"Unuseful clarity\"] --\nall the more disheartening,"},{"time":966862,"text":"at least to me."},{"time":968510,"text":"So okay, again, going back\ndown into the subway,"},{"time":972350,"text":"after this came out,"},{"time":974440,"text":"these are pictures that I took."},{"time":976460,"text":"Times Square subway station:"},{"time":978503,"text":"Coca-Cola has bought out\nthe entire thing for advertising. Okay?"},{"time":983681,"text":"And maybe some of you\nknow where this is going."},{"time":988660,"text":"Ahem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990438,"text":"\"You moved to New York\nwith the clothes on your back,"},{"time":993056,"text":"the cash in your pocket,\nand your eyes on the prize."},{"time":995640,"text":"You're on Coke.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":1005298,"text":"\"You moved to New York\nwith an MBA, one clean suit,"},{"time":1008251,"text":"and an extremely firm handshake."},{"time":1010341,"text":"You're on Coke.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":1013638,"text":"These are real! (Laughter)"},{"time":1018142,"text":"Not even the support beams were spared,"},{"time":1021973,"text":"except they switched into Yoda mode.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":1027569,"text":"\"Coke you're on.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":1031298,"text":"[\"Excuse me, I'm on WHAT??\"]"},{"time":1034018,"text":"This campaign was a huge misstep."},{"time":1037623,"text":"It was pulled almost instantly\ndue to consumer backlash"},{"time":1042310,"text":"and all sorts of unflattering\nparodies on the web --"},{"time":1046850,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":1048731,"text":"and also that dot next to \"You're on,\"\nthat's not a period, that's a trademark."},{"time":1055141,"text":"So thanks a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1056421,"text":"So to me, this was just so bizarre"},{"time":1060433,"text":"about how they could get the packaging\nso mysteriously beautiful and perfect"},{"time":1066447,"text":"and the message so unbearably,\nclearly wrong."},{"time":1070905,"text":"It was just incredible to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074365,"text":"So I just hope that I've been able\nto share with you some of my insights"},{"time":1079891,"text":"on the uses of clarity\nand mystery in my work,"},{"time":1083699,"text":"and maybe how you might decide\nto be more clear in your life,"},{"time":1089005,"text":"or maybe to be a bit more mysterious\nand not so over-sharing."},{"time":1095273,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099000,"text":"And if there's just one thing\nthat I leave you with from this talk,"},{"time":1103806,"text":"I hope it's this:"},{"time":1105757,"text":"Blih blih blih blah. Blah blah blih blih.\n[\"'Judge This,' Chip Kidd\"]"},{"time":1109022,"text":"Blih blih blah blah blah.\nBlah blah blah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1112086,"text":"Blah blah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113883,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}